      • addItems

        public ItemStack addItems(int count)
        Adds the specified amount of the items to the stack. The stack will be set to non-empty if the stack size is above zero. This will not increase the amount above the item's maximum stack size. This returns an item stack containing overflow items if the stack has become too large.
        Parameters:
        count - How many items to add
        Returns:
        the overflow items that exceed the maximum stack size
        See Also:

      • removeItems

        public ItemStack removeItems(int count)
        Removes the specified amount of the items to the stack. The amount will not decrease below zero. The stack will be set to empty if the stack size is zero. This returns an item stack containing overflow items, which should theoretically always be empty.
        Parameters:
        count - How many items to remove
        Returns:
        the overflow items that exceed the maximum stack size
        See Also:
        setAmount(int)

      • setAmount

        public ItemStack setAmount(int amount)
        Sets the stack size to the given amount. The stack will be set to empty or non-empty accordingly. Any negative size will be set to zero. Any value above the item's maximum stack size will be set to the maximum stack size.

        If the amount is set to greater than the max stack size, a new stack of the same item type will be returned containing the number of extra items. This may be an invalid number of items for an item of that type as it is not checked here. An empty stack of null items is returned if there are no extra items.

        Parameters:
        amount - How many items the stack should contain
        Returns:
        the overflow items that exceed the maximum stack size
